{% set basicTfootCode %}<table>
  <caption>Quarterly Sales Report</caption>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th scope="col">Product</th>
      <th scope="col" data-numeric>Q1</th>
      <th scope="col" data-numeric>Q2</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Widget A</td>
      <td data-numeric>$12,500</td>
      <td data-numeric>$15,200</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Widget B</td>
      <td data-numeric>$8,900</td>
      <td data-numeric>$9,500</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
  <tfoot>
    <tr>
      <td>Total</td>
      <td data-numeric>$21,400</td>
      <td data-numeric>$24,700</td>
    </tr>
  </tfoot>
</table>{% endset %}

{% set sourceOrderCode %}<table>
  <caption>...</caption>
  <colgroup>...</colgroup>
  <thead>...</thead>
  <tbody>...</tbody>
  <tfoot>...</tfoot>  <!-- After tbody -->
</table>{% endset %}

{% set tfootCss %}/* VB default tfoot styles */
tfoot td {
  font-weight: 600;
  background: var(--color-surface-raised);
  border-block-start: var(--border-width-medium)
    solid var(--color-border);
}{% endset %}

  <section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;tfoot&gt;</code> element contains one or more <a href="/docs/elements/native/tr/"><code>&lt;tr&gt;</code></a> elements that form the footer of a table. Place it after <a href="/docs/elements/native/tbody/"><code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code></a> in the source for clarity -- browsers render it at the bottom regardless of source position.</p>
    <p>Vanilla Breeze styles tfoot cells with <code>font-weight: 600</code>, a raised background (<code>var(--color-surface-raised)</code>), and a thicker top border (<code>var(--border-width-medium)</code>) to visually distinguish summary rows from data rows.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Summary totals:</strong> Sum, average, or count of column values</li>
      <li><strong>Aggregate data:</strong> Calculated values derived from <a href="/docs/elements/native/tbody/"><code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code></a> data</li>
      <li><strong>Financial tables:</strong> Final totals, subtotals, tax lines</li>
      <li><strong>Repeated footers:</strong> Printed tables can repeat tfoot on each page</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When Not Needed</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Simple tables:</strong> Tables without summary data do not require tfoot</li>
      <li><strong>Pagination controls:</strong> Navigation links belong outside the table, not in tfoot</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <h3>Table with Totals</h3>
    <p>The shared basic table demo includes a tfoot with totals row, showing the raised background and top border that VB applies automatically.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/table-basic.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/table/basic" title="Table with tfoot totals row" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Basic tfoot with totals">{{ basicTfootCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Source Order</h3>
    <p>Historically, tfoot could be placed before tbody in HTML to let browsers start rendering the footer early. Modern browsers handle this automatically. Place tfoot after tbody for more readable source:</p>
    <code-block language="html" label="Recommended source order">{{ sourceOrderCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <p>Vanilla Breeze applies these styles to cells within tfoot:</p>

    <code-block language="css" label="VB tfoot CSS">{{ tfootCss | escape }}</code-block>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Property</th>
          <th scope="col">Value</th>
          <th scope="col">Purpose</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>font-weight</code></td>
          <td><code>600</code></td>
          <td>Semi-bold to emphasize summary data</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>background</code></td>
          <td><code>var(--color-surface-raised)</code></td>
          <td>Raised surface to distinguish from body rows</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>border-block-start</code></td>
          <td><code>var(--border-width-medium) solid var(--color-border)</code></td>
          <td>Thicker border separating footer from body</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Semantic grouping:</strong> Helps assistive technologies identify summary rows as distinct from data</li>
      <li><strong>Implicit role:</strong> tfoot has an implicit ARIA role of <code>rowgroup</code></li>
      <li><strong>Navigation:</strong> Screen reader users can jump directly to the table footer</li>
      <li><strong>Clear labels:</strong> Use descriptive text like "Total" or "Average" in the first cell of each footer row</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

